<dt id="fieldsetlegend-Access"> Access </dt>

<dd id="fieldset-Access">
<table class="invisible two_column_table">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>
<h2>Access</h2>
<p> <span class="link-mailto"><a href="mailto:demorequest@bikalabs.com?subject=Access%20to%20Gaob%20Bika%20LIMS%203%20on-line%20installation"><u>Bika LIMS 3 demo request</u></a></span><strong><br /></strong></p>
<h2>Feedback</h2>
<p>Don't hesitate to post questions and comment to the Bika mailing lists: <a class="external-link" href="https://groups.google.com/forum/?hl=en#%21forum/bika-design">LIMS design</a>, <a class="external-link" href="http://lists.sourceforge.net/lists/listinfo/bika-users">Users</a> or <a class="external-link" href="http://lists.sourceforge.net/lists/listinfo/bika-developers">Developers</a>.</p>
<p>Please log issues, feature requests, or bug reports in the <a class="external-link" href="https://github.com/bikalabs/Bika-LIMS/issues">public issue tracker</a> at Github</p>
<h2 align="left" class="Subheading">Test data<br /></h2>
<p align="left">We've created a standardised open-XLSX<strong> </strong>spreadsheet to configure the LIMS with setup data of the user's choice. We populated this   instance with data of
 uniform   nature for most setup items, e.g. analysis specifications,
QC, uncertainties, turn-around time, precision, price   etc. See <a class="internal-link" href="setup-data-in-this-installation">Setup data used to configure this installation</a></p>
</td>
<td align="center"><img class="image-inline" src="++resource++bika.lims.images/miris.jpg" alt="Miris milk analyser" />
<p class="discreet"><br />Miris DMA - Dairy Milk Analyser<br /><a class="external-link" href="http://www.tridentinstrumentation.co.za/index.htm">Trident Instrumentation</a></p>
<br /></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</dd>

<dt id="fieldsetlegend-New"> New functions</dt>
<dd id="fieldset-New">
<table class="invisible two_column_table">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>
<p align="center"><a class="external-link" href="http://www.bikalabs.com/portfolio/umhlathuze"><img class="image-inline" src="http://www.bikalabs.com/images/umhlathuze" alt="Umhlathuze logo" /></a></p>
<p>New items sponsored by the water quality lab at the City of uMhlathuze, Richards Bay:</p>
<a class="external-link" href="bika_setup/bika_calculations">Results calculations</a>,
    including interim fields and dependent analyses, are user
   configurable and new calculations can be added by authorised
users<br /><br />
Dormant setup items can be de-activated, which will remove them from general view while maintaining database integrity. The same for sample and analysis request cancellation workflows<br /><br />
<p>  Plone 4's versioning is used to maintain references to historical data. Working copy support combined with  content locking  allow multiple users  access to data without conflicts</p>
<p> Using AJAX, Plone 4's user interface and a host of smaller enhancements, many clicks were saved and general performance improved</p>
</td>
<td>
<p align="center" class="callout"><strong>Where did all the columns go?</strong><br /><br />
<img class="image-inline" src="list-column-toggles" alt="List Column Toggles" /><br /><br />To facilitate small screen displays, users select which columns they want displayed on Samples, Analysis Request and Worksheet lists<br /><br /><strong>Right click </strong>on the column headers on these list to display the column display toggle menu<br /><br /></p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</dd>

